The paper deals with approximation algorithms for covering problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and optimization. The use of primal-dual algorithms and the focus on relaxation techniques suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The specific applications to power and transport systems suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
